      <list id="id4468542" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Each of the two patterns can be identified and a third is formed as a result of the combination of the first two. This technique is called hocketing: Although each party has its own individuality,<emphasis effect="bold"> co-operation</emphasis> and <emphasis effect="bold">interaction</emphasis> take place despite the <emphasis effect="bold">independence.</emphasis></item>
      </list>
